                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Selden_Supra_26-part9-item1">
                        <title type="desc" key="work_14469">Sacramentary</title>
                       
                        <note>Parts of leaves from a 10th or 11th cent. Sacramentary written at St. Omer (?) (see fol. 130r).</note>
                        <note>The first leaf contains: Iac. v, 17,18 and v, 19,20, followed by a badly damaged text (fol. 4v) and Ierem. v, 1, vi, 16 and 7, 3/7. The second leaf, at the end of the volume (fol. 130) has a prayer: Presta quesumus omnipotens deus ut ad te toto corde (St. Peter) and a series of orationes pro peccatis: Deus cui proprium; Da nobis quesumus domine de tribulatione … intercedente beato Audomaro in tua miseratione …; Clamantium ad te; Deus qui peccantium animas; Deus qui culpas delinquentium; Parce domine parce populo; Deus qui culpas nostras piis verberibus; Adesto domine supplicationibus nostris.</note>
                        <!-- 
                        <seg>MS. Selden supra 26 (3414)</seg>
<seg>ST. OMER (?)</seg>
<seg>10th century</seg>
</head>
<p>Two fly leaves; </p>
<p>Parchm., 2 fol., 177 x 115 mm.; at least 19 lines to a page, 155 (at least) x 80 mm.</p>
                        -->
                        <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
